Flow 1 — User Registration
START
  │
  ▼
User fills form (firstName, lastName, email, phone, password)
  │
  ▼
FluentValidation checks all fields
  ├── FAIL → Return 400 with all error messages
  │
  ▼
Check if email already exists in DB
  ├── EXISTS → Return 400 "Email already registered"
  │
  ▼
Check if phone already exists in DB
  ├── EXISTS → Return 400 "Phone already registered"
  │
  ▼
BCrypt hash the password (cost factor 11)
  │
  ▼
Create User entity + UserProfile entity
  │
  ▼
Save both to auth_db (single transaction)
  │
  ▼
Publish UserRegisteredEvent to RabbitMQ
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK with accessToken + refreshToken + user profile
  │
  ├──► [ASYNC] Wallet.API creates wallet (status = Pending)
  ├──► [ASYNC] Rewards.API creates loyalty account (Bronze tier)
  └──► [ASYNC] Notification.API sends welcome email

END

Flow 2 — Login
START
  │
  ▼
User submits email + password
  │
  ▼
Find user by email in auth_db
  ├── NOT FOUND → Write AuditLog (failed) → Return 401
  │
  ▼
Check IsActive = true
  ├── FALSE → Write AuditLog (failed) → Return 401
  │
  ▼
BCrypt.Verify(inputPassword, storedHash)
  ├── MISMATCH → Write AuditLog (failed) → Return 401
  │
  ▼
Generate JWT accessToken (60 min, HMAC-SHA256)
  │
  ▼
Generate RefreshToken (128-bit random, 7 days)
  │
  ▼
Save RefreshToken to auth_db
  │
  ▼
Write AuditLog (success)
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK with accessToken + refreshToken + user profile

END

Flow 3 — KYC Approval
START
  │
  ▼
User submits KYC (documentType, documentNumber, documentUrl)
  │
  ▼
Create KYCRecord (status = Submitted) in auth_db
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK — awaiting admin review
  │
  ▼
Admin calls GET /api/kyc/pending
  │
  ▼
Admin reviews and calls POST /api/kyc/{id}/approve
  │
  ▼
Update KYCRecord status = Approved
Set ReviewedBy = adminId
Set ReviewedAt = now
  │
  ▼
Publish KYCApprovedEvent to RabbitMQ
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK to admin
  │
  ├──► [ASYNC] Wallet.API sets wallet status = Active
  └──► [ASYNC] Notification.API sends KYC approval email

--- REJECTION PATH ---

Admin calls POST /api/kyc/{id}/reject (with reason)
  │
  ▼
Update KYCRecord status = Rejected
Set RejectionReason = reason
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK
  │
  └──► [ASYNC] Notification.API sends rejection email

END

Flow 4 — Fund Wallet
START
  │
  ▼
User calls POST /api/wallet/fund (amount, description)
  │
  ▼
Gateway validates JWT → routes to Wallet.API
  │
  ▼
Get wallet by userId from wallet_db
  ├── NOT FOUND → Return 404
  │
  ▼
Check wallet status
  ├── Pending → Return 400 "Complete KYC first"
  ├── Frozen  → Return 400 "Wallet is frozen"
  ├── Closed  → Return 400 "Wallet is closed"
  │
  ▼
wallet.Balance += amount
  │
  ▼
Save updated wallet to wallet_db
  │
  ▼
Publish WalletFundedEvent to RabbitMQ
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK with updated wallet balance
  │
  └──► [ASYNC] Notification.API sends fund confirmation

END

Flow 5 — Payment (Send Money)
START
  │
  ▼
User calls POST /api/transactions/pay
Header: Idempotency-Key: {unique-key}
Body: { recipientId, amount, description }
  │
  ▼
Gateway validates JWT → routes to Transaction.API
  │
  ▼
Look up idempotency key in DB (by key + senderId)
  ├── FOUND → Return cached transaction response (no processing)
  │
  ▼
Validate input
  ├── amount <= 0   → Return 400
  ├── sender == recipient → Return 400
  │
  ▼
Create Transaction record (status = Pending)
  │
  ▼
Save IdempotencyRecord to DB  ← MUST happen before ledger write
  │
  ▼
Update Transaction status = Processing
  │
  ▼
Calculate sender balance from ledger
(SUM of credits - SUM of debits for senderId)
  │
  ▼
Check sender balance >= amount
  ├── INSUFFICIENT → Jump to FAILURE PATH
  │
  ▼
Write two ledger entries atomically:
  Entry 1: DEBIT  senderId    amount  (balanceBefore / balanceAfter)
  Entry 2: CREDIT recipientId amount  (balanceBefore / balanceAfter)
  │
  ▼
Update Transaction status = Completed
  │
  ▼
Publish TransactionCompletedEvent to RabbitMQ
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK with transaction + ledger entries
  │
  ├──► [ASYNC] Rewards.API awards points to sender
  └──► [ASYNC] Notification.API sends payment confirmation

--- FAILURE PATH (Saga Compensation) ---

Any error after balance check
  │
  ▼
Update Transaction status = Failed (with reason)
  │
  ▼
Publish TransactionFailedEvent to RabbitMQ
  │
  ▼
Return 500/400 error to client
  │
  └──► [ASYNC] Wallet.API credits amount back to sender
       [ASYNC] Notification.API sends failure notification

END

Flow 6 — Points Redemption
START
  │
  ▼
User calls POST /api/redemption (catalogItemId)
  │
  ▼
Gateway validates JWT → routes to Catalog.API
  │
  ▼
Get catalog item by id
  ├── NOT FOUND → Return 404
  ├── IsActive = false → Return 400 "Item not available"
  ├── StockCount = 0 → Return 400 "Out of stock"
  │
  ▼
Create Redemption record (status = Pending)
  │
  ▼
Decrement StockCount by 1 (if not unlimited / -1)
  │
  ▼
Save to catalog_db
  │
  ▼
Publish RedemptionRequestedEvent to RabbitMQ
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK with redemption details
  │
  ▼
[ASYNC] Rewards.API receives RedemptionRequestedEvent
  │
  ▼
Check user loyalty account points >= pointsCost
  ├── INSUFFICIENT → Publish failure back to Catalog
  │                  Catalog restores StockCount + 1
  │                  Redemption status = Failed
  │
  ▼
Deduct pointsCost from TotalPoints
Write PointTransaction (type = Redeemed, negative points)
  │
  ▼
Generate VoucherCode (format: XXXX-XXXX-XXXX)
Update Redemption status = Completed
  │
  └──► [ASYNC] Notification.API sends redemption confirmation
       with voucher code

END

Flow 7 — Token Refresh
START
  │
  ▼
Client sends POST /api/auth/refresh-token
Body: { refreshToken: "..." }
  │
  ▼
Find RefreshToken record in auth_db
  ├── NOT FOUND → Return 401
  │
  ▼
Check token.IsExpired (DateTime.UtcNow >= ExpiresAt)
  ├── EXPIRED → Return 401
  │
  ▼
Check token.IsRevoked
  ├── REVOKED → Possible token theft — revoke ALL user tokens
  │             Return 401
  │
  ▼
Get user from token.UserId
  ├── IsActive = false → Return 401
  │
  ▼
Generate new accessToken (fresh 60 min)
Generate new refreshToken (fresh 7 days)
  │
  ▼
Mark old refreshToken as Revoked
Set old token.ReplacedBy = new token value
  │
  ▼
Save new refreshToken to auth_db
  │
  ▼
Return 200 OK with new accessToken + new refreshToken

END